JAPAN DAYBOOK: Japan Struggles to Stabilize Nuclear Reactor

-- B y   E d i t o r :   S t e v e n   M c P h e r s o n
-- 
2011-03-15T00:10:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/japan-daybook-japan-struggles-to-stabilize-nuclear-reactor.html
The government and Tokyo
Electric Power Co. are struggling to stabilize a nuclear
reactor, where an explosion was heard and a possible
radiation leak was reported. Meanwhile, thousands are still
without homes in the area following the earthquake and
tsunami that damaged the nuclear plant.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*The government and Tokyo Electric Power hold periodic
briefings on the status of a damaged nuclear plant.
*The number of confirmed deaths from the March 11 earthquake
and tsunami reached 1,897, with 3,002 missing as of midnight
last night.
  Japan  to order oil wholesalers to release reserves, Trade
 Minister  Banri Kaieda  said yesterday.
*Osaka Securities Exchange President Michio Yoneda gives a
 regular press conference 3:30 pm. The Tokyo Stock Exchange
 plans to hold merger talks with its Osaka counterpart.  CORPORATE EVENTS:
*Shimane Bank (7150 JP) shares trade on Tokyo Stock
 Exchange’s second section.
*ID Home (3274 JP) shares trade on Osaka Securities
 Exchange’s Jasdaq market.
 